ENTRY       EC 2.1.1.129                Enzyme
NAME        inositol 4-methyltransferase;
            myo-inositol 4-O-methyltransferase;
            S-adenosyl-L-methionine:myo-inositol 4-O-methyltransferase;
            myo-inositol 6-O-methyltransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring one-carbon groups;
            Methyltransferases
SYSNAME     S-adenosyl-L-methionine:1D-myo-inositol 4-methyltransferase
REACTION    S-adenosyl-L-methionine + myo-inositol = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + 1D-4-O-methyl-myo-inositol [RN:R01190]
ALL_REAC    R01190
SUBSTRATE   S-adenosyl-L-methionine [CPD:C00019];
            myo-inositol [CPD:C00137]
PRODUCT     S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine [CPD:C00021];
            1D-4-O-methyl-myo-inositol [CPD:C06352]
COMMENT     The enzyme from the rice bean Vigna umbellata (Fabaceae) is highly specific for S-adenosyl-L-methionine. The enzyme also methylates 1L-1,2,4/3,5-cyclohexanepentol, 2,4,6/3,5-pentahydroxycyclohexanone, D,L-2,3,4,6/5-pentacyclohexanone and 2,2'-anhydro-2-C-hydroxymethyl-myo-inositol, but at lower rates than that of myo-inositol.
HISTORY     EC 2.1.1.129 created 1999 (EC 2.1.1.134 created 1999, incorporated 2002), modified 2002
